cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about semantic segmentation in videos using convolutional gated recurrent networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel approach to utilize temporal data in videos, which involves the use of recurrent networks. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which may place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Finally, the paper proposes a method to improve the performance of a baseline segmentation network, which may suggest that it belongs to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
